metadata.name: Dencity #26
metadata.description:
Dencity is a generative art project inspired by aerial views of cities with a high density of buildings. Its perspective effect, its perfectly imprecise lines, its subtle textures and its very advanced level of detail give it the appearance of a hand-drawn work.

Behind the visible art (the image) hides another form of art, an extremely complex algorithm capable of calculating and drawing in 2D each variation of the Dencity project. To draw a variation, the algorithm notably takes around 3,000,000 to 20,000,000 random decisions based on the hash of the mint and draws around 800,000 to 4,000,000 lines to create all the strokes and texture effects.

Made with ❤️, code and p5js.

metadata.name: ASTRONOMICAL #45
metadata.description:
Define your own galaxy.
How will you choose to orient the numerous, or sparse, planets?
What palette might be the topic of discussion on the James Webb Space Telescope's next discovery? 
Mould your central planet into the next ASTRONOMICAL phenomenon.

Every aspect of every aspect is randomized: the location, opacity and size of stars. The colours, division, and size of the central planet. The number and location of curves, as well as the size, colour and number of planets along each one. The thickness of the border, and the strength of the effects.

100% chance of 1 ring, 10% chance of two rings and 1% chance of three rings around the central planet.

Made with p5.js.

metadata.name: Citta #38
metadata.description:
Citta as mind Citta as city. 

Citta is city of interconnected minds from future of Metropolis IX(Project id:13292), after singularity people uploaded their consciousness into inorganic self-constructing structures. 

There are 13 different mind-hives named with upper case letters, only "MC-00001" is monochrome rest is in color. "SCMB" and "SCCB' are in spiral formation due to their nature.

Press 1 to 8 export PNG 1000px to 8000px 
9 exports 10000px PNG 

Exports are dependent on CPU, so larger export might take time. Please be patient. If you cannot export reach me out.

Works best in Chrome browser. 

Created with p5.js and canvas api.
Murat Atimtay 2022 | @atimtay | www.muratatimtay.com

metadata.name: Artifact #155
metadata.description:
This project is about uncovering artifacts.

Each piece is determined by approximately 15 parameters. This allows for a multitude of possible forms, and each iteration is an artifact to be discovered within the multidimensional space.

This work is focused around discovery. It is about exploring the space of the algorithm, shedding light on its many forms, and sometimes finding artifacts of the real world embedded within them.

Technically, this work is a composition of three primary elements: Voronoi tessellations, orthographic projection, and the depth-sort algorithm.
The latter of these is integral to the rendering mechanism. It works intuitively, drawing distant objects before near objects, evaluating the distance of each object according to its geometric center. It does this precisely, and in doing so, it can produce interesting visual artifacts, drawing some shapes in an unexpected order.



This has been a fascinating study, bringing light to unreal shapes and forms, and uncovering artifacts in an impossible space.

I hope you enjoy it,
Nat Sarkissian





Technical Notes:
- Append “&mag=N” to the end of the URL in live mode to specify a resolution multiplier. It will render the image N times larger than the size of your window. If you have specified anything greater than 1, a download will start automatically once the rendering is done.

metadata.name: MONOLITH #158
metadata.description:
Very limited facts are known about these strange monolithic structures. Black, rectilinear, similar to obsidian stone but made of strange materials. According to legend, an ancient civilization of high intelligence, called the Explorers of Latent Space, distributed hundreds of monoliths throughout time and space in order to study the behavior of species in the infinite Universe.

Some say that it is the divine intelligence of God. Others say that, in spite of their objectual and material condition, the monoliths possess their own consciousness and an intelligence beyond the natural and artificial. Their purpose or objective, to this day, remains a mystery.

_-_-_-_-_-_-_-_

this work is done only with code, using threejs and p5js
it might be a bit slow on low-end devices, be patient
